  "StockRole": "Juggernaut",
  "YangsThoughts": "Created by Black Rooster Mechanical Development, (also knows as BRoMeD) as their first foray into the 100-ton 'Mech bracket, the Warlord took a lot of inspiration from the Pillager 5L in both appearance and weapons configuration. However, since Arrow IV systems were seen as too expensive, it was replaced by both a long and a short range missile launcher. The design was quickly challenged by Hellespont Industrials on Betelguese, the main supplier of Pillagers to the Capellan Confederation. After negotiations broke down, Hellespont started a very successful smear campaign that eventually drove the BRoMeD out of business. No more Warlords were produced, and some of the 'Mech's spare components are quite hard to find as a result.",
